2026-04-30T13:30Z claude created

--- body ---
## Context

Anthropic reportedly runs a nightly server-side pass over Claude memory
(dedup, merge, prune, regenerate index). Claude Code ships no native
equivalent.

Existing harness skills do partial memory work but are anchored to a recent
user-driven event:

- `/celebrate` pre-checks "branch merged into origin/main" and references
  "the task just completed" — meaningless when fired cold by a timer.
- `/end-session` reflects on `git log --since="6am"` and refreshes a single
  project's `STATE.md` — wrong scope (one repo) and wrong trigger (assumes
  same-day session).

The actual consolidation logic is a one-liner in step 10 of `/end-session`
("memory sweep — follow `/memory` skill"). The `/memory` skill is policy
(caps, TTLs, staleness criteria) without an LLM-driven dedup/merge pass.

Proposal: a new skill `/dream` that performs autonomous nightly
consolidation across all project memory dirs, runnable both manually and as
a `/schedule`-fired agent. `/celebrate` and `/end-session` remain
user-driven and task-scoped; `/dream` is the cross-project, cron-friendly
sibling.

## Design — patterns lifted from published OSS (initial survey)

- **Tool-call classifier over k-neighborhood** (mem0, arXiv 2504.19413).
  For each candidate fact, retrieve neighbors and force the LLM to emit one
  of `ADD | UPDATE | DELETE | NOOP`. Prevents silent dedup drift.
- **Recursive reflection** (Generative Agents, Park 2023, arXiv 2304.03442).
  After dedup, draft N higher-level insights from survivors and rewrite
  `MEMORY.md` from those.
- **Bi-temporal invalidation** (Zep / Graphiti, arXiv 2501.13956). Don't
  `rm`; rewrite in place — git history already gives bi-temporal recovery
  for free.
- **Sleep-time decoupling** (Letta, https://docs.letta.com/guides/agents/architectures/sleeptime).
  Run as a separate scheduled agent on a cheaper model against a frozen
  snapshot. Safe to abort. Default: haiku 4.5.
- **Importance-sum trigger** (Park) — optional v2; v1 is plain time-based.

## Actions

1. **Fresh deep-research pass before any code.** This is bleeding-edge — the
   above survey is from 2026-04-30 and the field is moving weekly. Before
   the implementer writes a line, re-run the literature pass: Letta sleep-time
   updates since 2026-Q1, mem0 ≥ v0.2 schema changes, A-MEM follow-ups,
   Anthropic blog/docs for any newly-public memory-management primitives,
   Cognee `memify` semantics, anything from NeurIPS / ICLR 2026. Reconcile
   with the patterns above; reject any pattern that's been retracted or
   superseded. Capture the second-round findings in a companion note
   (`docs/dream-research.md`) before opening the implementation PR.

2. Create `~/.claude/skills/dream/SKILL.md`. Frontmatter:
   `user-invocable: true`, description names "autonomous nightly memory
   consolidation".

3. Cross-project scope. The skill iterates over
   `~/.claude/projects/*/memory/`. For each project dir:
   a. Read `MEMORY.md` index + every memory file.
   b. For each entry, classify against neighbors via tool call
      (`ADD | UPDATE | DELETE | NOOP`). Apply staleness rules from `/memory`.
   c. Apply edits in place via `Edit`/`Write`. Never `rm` — leave a tombstone
      line if needed; git is the audit log.
   d. Regenerate `MEMORY.md` from the survivor set.
   e. Commit in IDH with `dream: consolidate <project> memory (<n>→<m>)`.

4. Refactor `/end-session` step 10 to call `/dream <current-project>`. Same
   single-project scope as today, but end-session and the timer share an
   implementation.

5. `/celebrate` unchanged — its current docs already say "save only, no
   sweep".

6. Trigger surface:
   - Manual: `/dream` (no args = sweep all projects; arg = project name).
   - Scheduled: document a `/schedule` recipe in the SKILL.md, e.g.
     `0 2 * * *` running `/dream` autonomously.

7. Idempotence + safety:
   - `/dream --dry-run` reports proposed edits without writing.
   - Skip projects with no memory-file mtime change since last consolidation
     marker (one-line log).
   - Default model haiku 4.5; allow override.
   - All git operations confined to IDH; never touch project repos.

8. Update `STATE.md` "Morning review" section to mention nightly
   consolidation and where to inspect the diff (`git log --grep='^dream:'`).

## Test (TDD red step)

Fixture project memory dir with two contradicting feedback entries added
on different dates ("use vim" / "use emacs"). Run `/dream --dry-run`.
Assert: older entry classified `DELETE`; newer survives; proposed
`MEMORY.md` drops the dead pointer; no files actually written.

## Exit criteria

- Second-round research note committed at `docs/dream-research.md`,
  reconciling the initial survey with current state of the art.
- `~/.claude/skills/dream/SKILL.md` exists, user-invocable, runs with no
  args.
- `/end-session` step 10 delegates to `/dream <project>`.
- `/schedule` recipe documented in SKILL.md (sample cron line, opt-in).
- Dry-run on the AEDIST project memory dir produces a sensible diff
  (manual review by the author before merge).
- At least one `dream: consolidate ...` commit appears in IDH history
  within one week of merge (proves the timer fires).

